OL,3,CLebanon wakes to a welcome but fragile
OL,4,Cpeace, many wonder if it will last
OL,6,FMany people in Lebanon woke up today
OL,7,Fafter their first truly restful
OL,8,Fnight's sleep in weeks.
OL,10,FThere were celebratory flares and
OL,11,Fgunfire as the ceasefire came into
OL,12,Fforce at midnight.
OL,14,FBut in the cold light of day, this war-
OL,15,Fweary nation faced the reality; this
OL,16,Fis a fragile truce in a country
OL,17,Fbattered by war.
OL,19,FSome of the million and more people
OL,20,Fdisplaced by the Israeli invasion have
OL,21,Fbegun the trek back to their homes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
