OL,3,CLebanon wakes to a welcome but fragile
OL,4,Cpeace, many wonder if it will last
OL,6,FWhat they're finding are smashed-up
OL,7,Fstreets and buildings reduced to
OL,8,Frubble.
OL,10,FThe clear-up operation will get
OL,11,Funderway ` but no one can tell how
OL,12,Flong this respite will last.
OL,14,FIsrael's army is still occupying a
OL,15,Fsecurity zone in the south. Hezbollah
OL,16,Fis as defiant as ever. This morning it
OL,17,Fwarned that its fighters ''will keep
OL,18,Ftheir hands on the trigger.''
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
